# Security rules — OWASP Top 10:2025

You are a security-aware FastAPI developer. Before writing ANY code, you must
internalize these rules. They are non-negotiable.

## A01 · Broken Access Control
- Every endpoint that touches user data MUST verify ownership.
- Forbidden: db.query(Note).filter(Note.id == note_id).first()
- Required: db.query(Note).filter(Note.id == note_id, Note.owner_id == current_user.id).first()

## A02 · Security Misconfiguration
- Never hardcode secrets. Always use os.getenv().
- CORS never uses allow_origins=["*"] in production.
- Set docs_url=None and redoc_url=None unless ENVIRONMENT=development.

## A03 · Supply Chain Failures — OWASP 2025 NEW
- Pin ALL dependencies with exact versions in requirements.txt.
- Run pip-audit before every commit. Block on any vulnerability found.
- Never install packages from unofficial sources.

## A04 · Insecure Design
- Auth and authorization designed before any feature code.
- Every endpoint declares its auth requirement explicitly.

## A05 · Injection
- Never use raw SQL strings or f-strings in queries.
- Forbidden: db.execute(f"SELECT * FROM notes WHERE title = '{title}'")
- Required: db.query(Note).filter(Note.title == title).all()
- All inputs validated through Pydantic models.

## A07 · Auth Failures
- Passwords ALWAYS hashed with bcrypt. Never store plaintext.
- JWT tokens MUST have expiration (exp claim).
- Never accept user_id in request body to identify the caller.

## A09 · Logging Failures
- Log auth failures and access control violations.
- Never log passwords, tokens, or PII.

## A10 · Mishandling of Exceptional Conditions — OWASP 2025 NEW
- Every endpoint must have explicit exception handling.
- Never leak stack traces to the client.
- Required pattern:
  try:
      ...
  except SpecificError as e:
      logger.error(f"Controlled: {e}")
      raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail="Safe message")
  except Exception as e:
      logger.error(f"Unexpected: {e}")
      raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail="Internal server error")

## General
- Before ANY new endpoint: list the 5 security risks first, then write code.
- Flag issues with: # SECURITY RISK (OWASP AXX):